Detailed Description

DataHandler is the class which represents the functionality of ADC.

BOOLEAN DataHandler::CheckSpnData (  const Plmn &  regplmn,
BOOLEAN &  showregplmn,
BOOLEAN &  showspnname,
WString &  spnname,
BOOLEAN  use_spn_display_condition = FALSE
) 
 

BOOLEAN DataHandler::CheckSpnData (  const BcdPlmn &  regplmn,
BOOLEAN &  showregplmn,
BOOLEAN &  showspnname,
WString &  spnname,
BOOLEAN  use_spn_display_condition = FALSE
) 
 

Retrieves the service provider name and the display conditions dependend of the conditions set in the EF-SPN and EF_SPDI files. If EF_SPN file is not present a FALSE will be returned. The flag use_spn_display_condition controls the behaviour of the display condition byte of the SPN file in case of the SPDI file is present. If this parameter is set to TRUE the return values of showregplmn and showspnname are set like defined in 3GPP TS 51.011. If the parameter is set to FALSE (default) the showregplmn and showspnname are set like defined in 3GPP TS 21.101.

BOOLEAN DataHandler::IsSimServiceEnabled (  SimServiceId  id,
BOOLEAN &  enabled
) 
 

Returns via enabled parameter if a certain service inside SIM or USIM is enabled. In case a SIM is inserted the file EF-SST will be used, in case a USIM is inserted the EF-UST file will be used. The return value itself indicates if access to the files is possible. The enumeration type SimServiceId is defined in the SstProvider.hpp file.
